notesStmt.note: Wrapped in a parchment leaf from Section XV, "De quatuor virtutibus," of the Declamationes de Colloquio Simonis cum Jesu of Geoffrey of Auxerre (Patrilogia Latina, Vol. 184, Col. 447C-447D) with decorated initials in red and blue penwork.

msItem.title: Sermons for the liturgical year, f. 1r
Three long sermons or tracts on the passion of Christ, f. 243r

supportDesc.extent: 322 leaves : 195 x 148 (143 x 102) mm. bound to 204 x 145 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (parchment) + i (paper) + 322 + i (parchment); [1-322]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 2 columns of 28-32 lines; ruled in ink.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a Gothic cursive script, with the main text in a single hand, quotations (f. 312r-318r) in a second hand, and sermons (f. 318r-322v) in a third hand.

binding.p: Contemporary leather over wooden boards, with brass studs.

origin.p: Written in Germany in the 15th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
